\begin_layout Standard
In this paper, we proposed a new method to derive the electrostatic potential
 (ESP) directly from the real-space electron density of KS-DFT orbitals,
 and combine it with the parallel code ParaGauss 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand cite
key "ParaGaussV3.1"

\end_inset

.
 In order to investigate the energetic accuracy, we applied the most recently
 reported PMV correction term with 3D RISM while the free energy functional
 of solutes are determined with four different representation of the solvated
 system: (1) The solutes are represented by the atomic partial charges assigned
 on each solute site, which are also tabulated in standard force field database
 as the Lennard--Jones (LJ) parameters in a MM manner (MM-RISM); (2) The
 free energy functional is perturbed by the first order perturbation theory
 manner (PT1-RISM); (3) The free energy functional is perturbed by the second
 order perturbation theory manner (PT2-RISM); (4) The free energy functional
 is determined self consistently with the relaxation of QM and RISM theory.
\end_layout

